Odd-level SU(2) rank-four orbit transport certificate
Date: 2026-07-22 UTC

Build
-----
$ make -B -j1 verify_su2_odd_orbit_rank4_transport
g++ -O2 -std=c++20 -Wall -Wextra -Wpedantic -Wconversion \
    -Wsign-conversion -Wshadow -Werror \
    verify_su2_odd_orbit_rank4_transport.cpp \
    -o verify_su2_odd_orbit_rank4_transport

Exact all-exponent certificate
------------------------------
$ ./verify_su2_odd_orbit_rank4_transport
SU2_ODD_ORBIT_RANK4_TRANSPORT chambers=30 \
    pointwise_chambers=19 exact_base_points=30 direct_regimes=161 \
    exact_peeled_points=5 tail_regimes=4 two_cone_regimes=6 \
    shifted_two_cone_regimes=3 strip_regimes=18 \
    strip_peeled_points=24 unresolved_regimes=0 result=PASS

This is not a bounded exponent scan.  For each support/sign/parity chamber,
write every positive exponent as its minimum parity representative plus
twice a nonnegative residual exponent.  The verifier stratifies by the
support of the residual exponent vector.  It then proves the complete
residual orthant by fractional transport from negative spectral pairs to
positive spectral pairs whose squared bases dominate coordinatewise.
Capacitated Hall inequalities certify the existence of every transport.

Four one-variable regimes require finite peeling before tail transport.
Six regimes use the cones r_1>=r_3 and r_3>=r_1 directly.  Three require a
common shift followed by the same cone split; their eighteen boundary
strips reduce to one-variable transported tails.  All thirty chamber base
points and all twenty-nine peeled points are evaluated directly with exact
integer fusion arithmetic.

The spectral values other than the rational node -1 are roots of
X^3-3X+1.  The verifier proves their rational isolating intervals by exact
endpoint signs and derivative bounds.  All subsequent interval operations,
base comparisons, capacities, and Hall inequalities use arbitrary-precision
rational arithmetic.  No floating-point comparison contributes to PASS.

Independent rectangular validation
----------------------------------
$ ./search_su2_odd_orbit_gks rectangular-depth 4 30
SU2_ODD_ORBIT_RECTANGULAR_DEPTH rank=4 level=7 maximum_power=30 \
    words=226981 corner_entries=226981 boundary_entries=907924 \
    zero_corners=98612 zero_boundary_entries=98649 \
    minimum_corner=0@target0:[+3] \
    minimum_positive_corner=1@target0:[] \
    minimum_boundary=0@target1:[] \
    minimum_positive_boundary=1@target0:[] result=PASS

This second program evolves the integral orbit fusion ring directly and
checks every exponent in the rectangular box, every support-disjoint sign
choice, the scalar corner, and all four boundary coefficients.  It is a
bounded implementation cross-check; the transport certificate above is the
arbitrary-length proof.
